premise_source_doc_sentence: Allan  (  also Alan  )  Aynesworth  (  14 April 1864 , Sandhurst , Berkshire -- 22 August 1959 , Camberley , Surrey  )  is the stage name of a British actor whose career spanned almost six decades , including a lead part in the 1895 world premiere of Oscar Wilde 's The Importance of Being Earnest and his final role as the elderly Lord Lancaster in the movie The Last Days of Dolwyn  (  1949  )  .
